# RatVantage

Fedora-native Lenovo Legion hardware control — daemon + GTK4 dashboard + StatusNotifier tray.
Full project guide: see **AGENTS.md**. This file covers Cursor-specific behaviour.

## Crate layout

| Crate | Path | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `legion-common` | `crates/legion-common/` | Shared types, no side effects |
| `legion-probe` | `crates/legion-probe/` | Read-only sysfs/hwmon discovery |
| `legion-control-daemon` | `crates/legion-daemon/` | Root daemon, D-Bus, polkit gate |
| `legion-control-ui` | `crates/legion-ui/` | GTK4 dashboard (`gtk-ui` feature) |
| `legion-control-tray` | `crates/legion-tray/` | StatusNotifier tray |
| `ratvantage-test-support` | `crates/test-support/` | D-Bus fixture helpers |

## Required before every commit

```bash
cargo fmt --all                                              # CI rejects any formatting diff
cargo test --workspace                                       # all tests must pass
cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings    # zero warnings
```

CI runs all three. A formatting diff is the most common cause of CI failure — always run
`cargo fmt --all` last, right before committing.

## Testing without real hardware

All tests use sysfs fixture trees. Primary fixture:
`tests/fixtures/sysfs-82wm-confirmed/`

```bash
cargo run -p legion-probe -- --json --sysfs-root tests/fixtures/sysfs-82wm-confirmed
scripts/run-local-session-app.sh --frontend menu-check
```

## Non-negotiable safety rules

1. **GUI never runs as root** — all sysfs writes go through the polkit-gated daemon only
2. **No hardcoded `hwmonN` paths** — use dynamic discovery via the capability registry
3. **No raw sysfs writes** from UI or tray code
4. **Default to read-only** — write paths need validators + rollback before enabling
5. **No raw WMI/EC writes** or overclocking controls
